        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 5:35AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 535 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Austonio, moving north at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Crockett, Austonio, Grapeland, Lovelady, Kennard, Latexo, Weches,
Pennington, and Mound City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
